# Look at the county data
head(popdata)
## # A tibble: 6 × 2
##   County         Population
##   <chr>               <dbl>
## 1 los angeles      10081570
## 2 san diego         3316073
## 3 orange            3168044
## 4 riverside         2411439
## 5 san bernardino    2149031
## 6 santa clara       1927470
# Wrangle the data. Make the column names the same to join the two datasets.

CApop_county<-popdata %>%
  select("subregion" = County, Population)  %>% # rename the county col
  inner_join(counties) %>%
  filter(region == "california") # some counties have same names in other states
## Joining with `by = join_by(subregion)`
## Warning in inner_join(., counties): Each row in `x` is expected to match at most 1 row in `y`.
## ℹ Row 1 of `x` matches multiple rows.
## ℹ If multiple matches are expected, set `multiple = "all"` to silence this
##   warning.
head(CApop_county)
## # A tibble: 6 × 7
##   subregion   Population  long   lat group order region

## 3 los angeles   10081570 -118.  34.8   175  7829 california

# Map of CA population by county with seastars
# Add a geom_point layer.
ggplot()+
geom_polygon(data = CApop_county, 
             aes(x = long, 
                 y = lat, 
                 group = group,
                 fill = Population),  
             color = "black")+
  geom_point(data = stars, # add a point at all my sites
             aes(x = long,
                 y = lat))+
  coord_map()+
  theme_void() +
  scale_fill_gradient(trans = "log10")

# Make points proportional to number of stars.
ggplot()+
geom_polygon(data = CApop_county, 
             aes(x = long, 
                 y = lat, 
                 group = group,
                 fill = Population),  
             color = "black")+
  geom_point(data = stars, # add a point at all my sites 
             aes(x = long, 
                 y = lat,
                 size = star_no))+
  coord_map()+
  theme_void() +
  scale_fill_gradient(trans = "log10")

# Make a better legend label.
ggplot()+
geom_polygon(data = CApop_county, 
             aes(x = long, 
                 y = lat, 
                 group = group,
                 fill = Population),  
             color = "black")+
  geom_point(data = stars, # add a point at all my sites 
             aes(x = long, 
                 y = lat,
                 size = star_no))+ 
  coord_map()+
  theme_void() +
  scale_fill_gradient(trans = "log10")+
  labs(size = "# stars/m2")
